chunk.text: All workers must wear appropriate safety equipment including hard hats, safety glasses, and steel-toed boots when working in construction areas.
chunk.title: Safety Equipment Requirements

chunk.text: Any workplace incident must be reported within 24 hours to the safety coordinator. This includes near-misses, injuries, and equipment damage.
chunk.title: Incident Reporting Procedures

chunk.text: Employees returning from medical leave must provide medical clearance and may require gradual return-to-work accommodations.
chunk.title: Return to Work Guidelines

chunk.text: In case of emergency, all personnel must evacuate via designated routes and assemble at the primary muster point in the parking lot.
chunk.title: Emergency Evacuation Plan

chunk.text: Chemical substances must be stored in appropriate containers, labeled correctly, and handled only by trained personnel with proper PPE.
chunk.title: Chemical Handling Protocols
